  <Docs>
    <remarks>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>When sorting is enabled by setting the <see cref="P:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.AllowSorting" /> property of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid" /> control to true, <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.LinkButton" /> controls are rendered in the header of each column that has the <see cref="P:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridColumn.SortExpression" /> property set. (For automatically generated columns, the <see cref="P:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridColumn.SortExpression" /> property contains the same value as the data field.) These links allow you to sort the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid" /> control by the selected column. The <see cref="E:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.SortCommand" /> event is raised when a <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.LinkButton" /> control is clicked.</para>
      <para>For a list of initial property values for an instance of <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs" />, see the <see cref="M:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridSortCommandEventArgs.#ctor(System.Object,System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridCommandEventArgs)" /> constructor.</para>
      <para>For more information about handling events, see <format type="text/html"><a href="d98fd58b-fa4f-4598-8378-addf4355a115">Events and Delegates</a></format>.</para>
    </remarks>
    <summary>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>Provides data for the <see cref="E:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.SortCommand" /> event of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid" /> control. This class cannot be inherited.</para>
    </summary>
